  <div class="xhr_comment_photo">
    	<a alt="Checkman" href="/user/show/5117003-checkman"><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591798821p1/5117003.jpg" alt="5117003" /></a>
  </div>
  <div class="xhr_comment_body">
    <a style="font-weight:bold" href="/user/show/5117003-checkman">Checkman</a>

      
<span id="freeTextContainer7018267769161365652">&quot;it was the United States Navy’s “finest hour,” a heartening epic of an outgunned and outnumbered force sacrificing their lives for the greater good. </span>
  <span id="freeText7018267769161365652" style="display:none">"it was the United States Navy’s “finest hour,” a heartening epic of an outgunned and outnumbered force sacrificing their lives for the greater good. On the other hand, it was an embarrassing near-catastrophe borne out of gross tactical negligence that sent a lot of good men to the bottom of the Philippine Sea " Bullseye. In the winter/spring of 1991 I attended the Armor Officer Basic Course at Fort Knox, Kentucky. I met a full bird colonel who had been awarded the Distinguished Service Cross (just below the Medal of Honor) when he was a Second Lieutenant in South Vietnam circa 1970. I was very impressed with that medal. He took pity on the hero worshiping Second Lieutenant (me) and explained that medals are something that are given out, when things get screwed up, to the unlucky people people who find themselves in the middle of the storm. Hopefully Lieutenant you will never recieve when of these medals because everyone will do their job and luck will be on your side. I prefer that young lieutenants have no medals on their chests. I met him just a day or two after the air phase of Desert Storm had begun so combat was very much on our minds. Especially as armor (tank) officers. Excellent observation. Medals and accolades don't go to the company executive officer who always gets food, fuel and ammo to the troops. Books aren't written about that officer. Well at least not the type of book that goes on best seller lists.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7018267769161365652" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

    <br/>

    <span class="xhrCommentFooter greyText">
      Jul 26, 2021 08:55PM
    </span>

  </div>
  <div class="clear"></div>
</div>

</div>

